The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks for feature extraction and classification of images, specifically for action recognition in videos. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The exploration of architecture and hyperparameters also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of the UCF Sports Action dataset and mention of other image datasets suggests a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
